This paper deals with natural language processing and sentiment analysis, which are core topics in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves developing an automatic technique to reproduce psychological measurements on a large population, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.SI). The use of sentiment analysis and language-based techniques also relates to the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper involves analyzing data from social media, which falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SD).
